Two people are missing after a boat capsized while sailing on a lake in Devon. A major search mission is underway after the incident this afternoon on Roadford Lake. Two people were raced to Derriford Hospital in Plymouth. Their conditions are currently unclear. Two others were pulled out of the water and discharged after being checked over by medics. All of those involved are believed to be adults. Fire, ambulance, coastguard and air ambulance crews are at the scene. The boat has been recovered by emergency services. There were reportedly strong winds on the lake at the time the vessel capsized. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.